<p style="margin-top:10px; font-size:20px;">
    Binary trees are a subset of tree data structures. It is a tree structure where there are at most two branches off of any one node and for ever node X all items in its left subtree are smaller than X and the items in the right
    subtree are larger than X. As we can see from the tree on the right in the figure, because there is a 7 in the right subtree of 2 this is no longer a binary tree. Binary trees are mostly
    used for searching because they have an average depth on the order of log<sub>2</sub>(N).
</p>

